Women and men reached parity on college campuses in the United States in 1980. For the first time, just as many women graduated as men. In 1984, the year the Macintosh was launched, women in tech reached a high point, receiving nearly 40 percent of computer science degrees. Today, that percentage has been nearly cut in half. Why are women so underrepresented in technology fields? Emily Chang, long-time host of Bloomberg Technology explores.

